DETATILED CONNECTION:

LCD Display (16x2):

VSS (Pin 1): This is the ground pin. Connect it to any GND pin on your Arduino.
VDD (Pin 2): This is the power pin. Connect it to the 5V pin on your Arduino.
VO (Pin 3): This pin is used to adjust the contrast of the display. Connect it to the middle pin of a potentiometer (10k ohm), with the other two pins connected to 5V and GND.
RS (Pin 4): This is the register select pin. Connect it to digital pin 12 on your Arduino.
RW (Pin 5): This is the read/write pin. Connect it to GND if you are only writing to the display.
E (Pin 6): This is the enable pin. Connect it to digital pin 11 on your Arduino.
D4 to D7 (Pins 11 to 14): These are the data pins. Connect them to digital pins 5, 4, 3, and 2 on your Arduino, respectively.
A (Pin 15): This is the anode pin for the backlight. Connect it to the 5V pin on your Arduino.
K (Pin 16): This is the cathode pin for the backlight. Connect it to any GND pin on your Arduino.

DHT11 Temperature and Humidity Sensor:

VCC: This is the power pin. Connect it to the 5V pin on your Arduino.
GND: This is the ground pin. Connect it to any GND pin on your Arduino.
Data Out: This is the data pin. Connect it to digital pin 2 on your Arduino.
MAX30100 Pulse Oximeter Sensor:

VCC: This is the power pin. Connect it to the 5V pin on your Arduino.
GND: This is the ground pin. Connect it to any GND pin on your Arduino.
SDA: This is the serial data pin. Connect it to the A4 pin on your Arduino (SDA).
SCL: This is the serial clock pin. Connect it to the A5 pin on your Arduino (SCL).

BMP280 Pressure Sensor:

VCC: This is the power pin. Connect it to the 3.3V pin on your Arduino.
GND: This is the ground pin. Connect it to any GND pin on your Arduino.
SDA: This is the serial data pin. Connect it to the A4 pin on your Arduino (SDA).
SCL: This is the serial clock pin. Connect it to the A5 pin on your Arduino (SCL).

GSM Module (SoftwareSerial):

RX: This is the receive pin. Connect it to digital pin 10 on your Arduino.
TX: This is the transmit pin. Connect it to digital pin 9 on your Arduino.
VCC: This is the power pin. Connect it to the 5V pin on your Arduino.
GND: This is the ground pin. Connect it to any GND pin on your Arduino.

Other Connections:

Connect the 5V and GND pins on your Arduino to the respective power and ground rails on your breadboard to provide power to the sensors and the LCD display.
Connect the SDA and SCL pins on your Arduino to the corresponding pins on the sensors (e.g., MAX30100 and BMP280) for I2C communication.
